    "text": [
        "Nowadays speaking a foreign language plays an important role in our daily life some specialists  think that it is better for children to study another language at primary school rather than  junior or senior school. In my opinion, I think the advantages of this  outweigh the disadvantages.",
        "On the one hand, learning a foreign language at primary school may decrease the ability to speak the mother language for children. The time in  primary school plays an essential part in developing the abilities to speak the native language for kids. They need to spend lots of time practising their mother language. So if they need to distinguish a part of their time to learning a foreign language it will reduce the chance for the kids to speak their mother language.",
        "On the other hand, there are some advantages for children learning a foreign language in primary school. Firstly, the speed of learning a foreign language is faster in younger children, which can save lots of time. Secondly, the pressure of study is lower in primary school because the students in secondary school have lots of work from their teachers  they do not have enough time to study a foreign language, which may cause a poor quality of learning.",
        "To summarize, although learning a foreign language in primary school may reduce the chance for students house their mother language, the speed of learning a foreign language is faster  in younger children and the pressure of study in primary school is much lower than in secondary school, which can improve the quality of learning a foreign language. So, in my opinion, I think the advantage of learning a foreign language in primary school outweigh the disadvantages."
